batchBalanceAndTradeActionWithCallback(a.notice: Executes a batch of balance transfers and trading actions via an authorized callback contract. This can be used as a "flash loan" facility for special contracts that migrate assets between protocols or perform other actions on behalf of the user. Contracts can borrow from Notional and receive a callback prior to an FC check, this can be useful if the contract needs to perform a trade or repay a debt on a different protocol before depositing collateral. Since Notional's AMM will never be as capital efficient or gas efficient as other flash loan facilities, this method requires whitelisting and will mainly be used for contracts that make migrating assets a better user experience.
